pros:
With awesome safety and health culture, in fact, safety is the company's number one priority -- you don't need to go to work if there's perceived danger. In terms of health, the company and the leadership teams are very committed -- you wil be sent to the clinic or home if they see that you're not feeling well;
Provides shuttle service for midshifters; Recognizes diversity and values inclusiveness; Speaking up your mind is encouraged;
Not strict, with free wifi and you can use your phones even during working hours;
Too many materials and courses that staff can browse and enroll to for free to develop skills relevant to their roles;
Provides recreational facilities i.e. billiards, videoke, gym, sleeping lounge etc.;
Management is very committed to ensuring a work-life-balance among staff
Competitive salary;
Overall, friendly working environment

cons:
Too many meetings during the day;
Shuttles for midshifters are on first-come-first-serve basis (but staff can reimburse taxi expense);
One of Shell's core values 'Respect for People' is sometimes ignored by few staff;
Graduate Hires are more favored by the managent in terms of promotion (but G-hires are really doing great and most of them are really capable of and with great potential; but those who are more tenured and also capable lose their chance for promotion)
